bilingual.source: Only men who own land can vote.
bilingual.target: 只有拥有土地的男人可以投票。

bilingual.source: He cooled the land, and then he began to rain.
bilingual.target: 他使土地变凉，然后开始下雨。

bilingual.source: A farmer found an ancient sculpture on his land.
bilingual.target: 一个农民在他的土地上发现了古雕塑。

bilingual.source: There is a way that nature speaks, that land speaks.
bilingual.target: 大自然有一种说话的方式，土地在说话。

bilingual.source: There are few large, flat areas of land in the region.
bilingual.target: 该地区几乎没有大块的平坦土地。

bilingual.source: More land is also used for growing crops or keeping livestock.
bilingual.target: 更多的土地也被用来种植农作物或饲养牲畜。

bilingual.source: When Columbus landed in the New World, he claimed the land for Spain.
bilingual.target: 哥伦布到达新大陆时，他为西班牙宣称了这片土地。

bilingual.source: Those without outside space can rent small pieces of land on which to grow things.
bilingual.target: 没有外部空间的人可以租用小块土地来种植东西。

bilingual.source: During the war, this land became a no man's land.
bilingual.target: 在战争期间，这片土地成了无人区。
这片土地有肥沃的土壤。

list.abstract: Land（[lænd]），英语单词，作名词为陆地；国家；阳膛线。作动词为使登岸；降落，着陆；使处于。短语搭配有Land Registry（地政局）。例句为“This is the land of opportunity（这是一片充满机遇的土地）”。 Land的过去分词为landed。复数为lands。第三人称单数为lands。

yingyinNormal.en: And that this, this is our land!
yingyinNormal.zh: 而这里，这是我们的土地。

yingyinNormal.en: Wherever Gul'dan works his magic, the land dies.
yingyinNormal.zh: 古尔丹在哪施魔法，哪里的土地便枯竭了。

yingyinNormal.en: That battle had only just begun, and some years later that land became ours, and the name of that land was Texas! Stop it!
yingyinNormal.zh: 而那场战争才仅仅是个开始，几年后，那块土地归属了我们，那块土地的名字就是，德克萨斯州！住手！

yingyinNormal.en: You mean, you want to farm the land yourself. Then it's all settled.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您是说，你们要自己管理那片土地，这都定下来了。

yingyinNormal.en: So, what if this whole chunk of land is connected to our tectonic plate?
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以，要是，要是这一大片土地都与地壳板块相连呢？

yingyinNormal.en: They got walls, fences, plots of land for farming. We could live there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们有围墙栅栏，可供耕种的土地，我们可以住在那里。

yingyinNormal.en: China's vast and varied land has helped shape a nation and its people.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国得广袤土地囊括万象，孕育了这个国家，养育了它的人民。

yingyinNormal.en: The fairy kingdom is the greatest secret of this land. Our duty is to protect it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 精灵王国是这片土地上最大的秘密，我们的责任就是保护它。

yingyinNormal.en: In your world, people are used to fighting for resources, like oil, or minerals, or land.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的世界里人们为各种资源而战，例如石油、矿产、土地。

yingyinNormal.en: The zoo was never ours to sell, the land belongs to the town. But the animals are ours.
yingyinNormal.zh: 动物园本来就不是我们的，土地都是国有的，但是动物是咱们的。

yingyinNormal.en: Are these the same landed gentry whose land you stripped against my husband's wishes not long ago?
yingyinNormal.zh: 和不久前那群因为违抗我夫君意愿而被你剥夺土地的地主 是同一群人吗？

yingyinNormal.en: China, a vast land, with one of the most diverse cultures on earth, now revealed like never before.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国，一片广袤的土地，有着世界上最多元的文化，正绽放着前所未有的光芒。

yingyinNormal.en: By all means warn him, I have spent enough elvish blood in defense of this accursed land, no more.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你务必警告他，我已牺牲太多精灵来守卫这片被诅咒的土地了，我不会再继续。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies》

yingyinNormal.en: For nearly 60 years, this humble patch of earth on the outskirts of town has been transformed into a frozen fantasy land.
yingyinNormal.zh: 近60年来，哈尔滨郊外这块不起眼的土地变身成为一块冰封的梦幻世界。

yingyinNormal.en: So I will hear arguments now on the fact of Ed's seeds being planted on Wendell's land, not just the intent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我现在会基于艾德的种子种植在温德尔土地上这一事实，听取辩论，不只是看个人意愿。

yingyinNormal.en: Thousands of miles from the comfort zone of your shopping malls, who sent your Porge to be blown to bits in our land, or better yet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 和你们那些舒适惬意的商场相距千万里，你们把穷人送到我们的土地上当靶子。

yingyinNormal.en: Look! It's snowing! It's snowing! The Queen has cursed this land! She must be stopped! You have to go after her... Wait, no!
yingyinNormal.zh: 看！下雪了！下雪了！皇后诅咒了这片土地！一定要阻止她！你得追上她，等下，不！

yingyinNormal.en: Over the centuries, those living in the remotest places have had to come up with ingenious methods to make the most of the land.
yingyinNormal.zh: 数百年来，生活在偏远地区的人们必须想出独具一格的方法才能让土地得到最大限度的利用。

yingyinNormal.en: Groups of people that shared a single language and culture often split into smaller tribes, going separate ways in search of fresh game and fertile land.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拥有同一种语言文化的族群通常分裂为更小的部落，分头各自寻找野味和肥沃的土地。

yingyinNormal.en: Highways stretching north from Dallas lured people out to the cheap land and open space of Arlington and other suburbs like this one, Colleyville.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从达拉斯延伸到北部的高速公路引诱着人们离开到这些廉价的土地来，像阿林顿的开放空间和像科利维尔一样的郊区。

examination_example.sentence: The colonists' first glimpse of the new <highlight>land</highlight> was a sight of dense woods.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 殖民者第一眼看到的是新大陆上的茂密树林。

examination_example.sentence: Rather than portraying landscape, <highlight>land</highlight> artists used the physical substance of the <highlight>land</highlight> itself as their medium.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大地艺术家不是在描绘风景，而是把大地本身的物质实体作为他们的艺术材料。

examination_example.sentence: British <highlight>Land</highlight> Art was a kind of landscape-orientated light conceptual art.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国大地艺术是一种以景观为导向的光概念艺术。

sense_info_list.en: an area of ground, especially of a particular type or used for a particular purpose
sense_info_list.zh: 土地; 田地; 地带

examination_example.sentence: Just 25 per cent of the country's <highlight>land</highlight> is suitable for crop-growing, most of which is already occupied by arable fields.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该国只有25%的土地适合种植农作物，其中大部分已经被耕地占用。

examination_example.sentence: Typically, if rains are delayed, people may clear <highlight>land</highlight> to plant more rice to supplement their harvests.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通常情况下，如果降雨延迟，人们可能会清理土地，种植更多的水稻以补充收成。

examination_example.sentence: There, as people got more money, some of them may have more cleared <highlight>land</highlight> for cattle to raise for meat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在那里，随着人们获得更多的钱，其中一些人可能会拥有更多的空地来养牛吃肉。

sense_info_list.en: cause someone to be in a difficult or unwelcome situation or task
(of something unpleasant or unexpected) arrive suddenly
the countryside and the way people live in the country as opposed to in cities
bring a fish to land, especially with a net or hook

examination_example.sentence: In contrast, the small cultivator is working only a few acres of <highlight>land</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，小耕农只耕种几英亩土地。

examination_example.sentence: If the farm is well managed and has enough <highlight>land</highlight>, and the desire to convert is sincere, a relationship can begin.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果农场管理得当且有足够的土地，并且真诚地希望转变，就可以开始一段合作关系。

examination_example.sentence: These practices include grazing animals on grasses grown from the pasture <highlight>land</highlight>'s natural seed bank, and fertilized by the comedown fertilizer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些实践包括在富有天然种子的牧场上放牧，和用动物自己的肥料施肥。

examination_example.sentence: Though he didn't come from a farming family, from a young age Tim Joseph was fascinated by the idea of living off the <highlight>land</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然他并不是来自农家，但从小 Tim Joseph 就被靠务农为生的理念所吸引。

examination_example.sentence: A car that takes off from some London street and <highlight>lands</highlight> in another random street is unlikely to happen.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一辆汽车从伦敦的某条街上起飞，然后降落在另一条随机的街上是不太可能发生的。

examination_example.sentence: The battle is currently being waged on <highlight>land</highlight>, in greenhouses at the University of Barcelona.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这场战斗目前正在陆地上，即巴塞罗那大学的温室里进行。

sense_info_list.zh: 搞到; 弄到; 捞到; 找到

examination_example.sentence: Workers at the Root Glass Company got the request and began flipping through the encyclopedia at the local library, <highlight>landing</highlight> on cocoa seed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Root Glass 公司的工作人员收到了请求，开始在当地图书馆翻阅百科全书，最终找到了可可种子。

word_usage.usage: land作“土地、地产”时是不可数名词，表示“三片土地”时，应说three pieces of land。

land表示“国家，国土”时，是可数名词，其前常用介词in。
He travelled in many lands.
他在许多国家旅行过。

land作“上岸，着陆”时是不及物动词，后面如跟宾语，要加相应的介词。
示例：我们降落在芝加哥机场。
We landed at the airport in Chicago.

examination_example.sentence: Farmers complain that <highlight>land</highlight> is being taken out of use by generously subsidised tree plantations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 农民们抱怨土地被慷慨补贴的树木种植园占用。

examination_example.sentence: This is the <highlight>land</highlight> of opportunity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是一片充满机遇的土地。

examination_example.sentence: The biggest concern of pumping out water from this deep in the gradual settling down of the <highlight>land</highlight> surface.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从这么深的地方抽水，最大的问题是土地表面逐渐沉降。

sense_info_list.en: the part of the earth's surface that is not covered by water; as opposed to the sea or the air

examination_example.sentence: Forests are gradually taking more <highlight>land</highlight> in America and Australia.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在美国和澳大利亚，森林正逐渐占据更多的土地。

examination_example.sentence: The village's roughly 650 residents have seen warming temperatures melt sea ice and permanently frozen <highlight>land</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这个村庄大约650名居民目睹了气候变暖融化了海冰和永久冻结的土地。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>land</highlight> has been connected to the network of lakes and streams in the area.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这片陆地与该地区的湖泊和溪流相连。

examination_example.sentence: It had one of its cargo planes <highlight>land</highlight> at a wrong airport.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这让一架货机误降在了别的机场。

examination_example.sentence: While ones in physics say: "How can you predict where the ball you tossed will <highlight>land</highlight>? "
examination_example.sentence_trans: 而物理学中的课文则说：“你怎么能预测你抛出的球会落在哪里？”

examination_example.sentence: Many patients also gained a better understanding of the illnesses that <highlight>landed</highlight> them in the hospital in the first place.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多患者也对最初让他们住进医院的疾病有了更好的了解。

examination_example.sentence: They decided in a vote of 89 to 78 to move from their <highlight>land</highlight> on Sarichef Island, near the Arctic Circle.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们以89票对78票决定从北极圈附近的沙里切夫岛(Sarichef Island)迁出。

examination_example.sentence: If someone is making up some conversation that might be interesting, it's probably not going to <highlight>land</highlight> well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果有人编造了一些有趣的对话，可能不会有好结果。

examination_example.sentence: In 1844 they bought it for $1,200 and some <highlight>land</highlight> from Charles Dresser, who performed their marriage ceremony in 1842.

examination_example.sentence: When the explorers set foot upon the continent of North America, the skies and <highlight>lands</highlight> were alive with an astonishing variety of wildlife.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当探险家们踏上北美大陆的时候，天空和陆地上充满了各种各样令人吃惊的野生动物。

examination_example.sentence: This <highlight>land</highlight> will be protected and available for all generations to come.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这片土地将受到保护，世世代代都可以使用。

examination_example.sentence: At 21, I <highlight>landed</highlight> a job at a big insurance company out of my business degree.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 21岁时，我凭借商学学位在一家大型保险公司找到了一份工作。

examination_example.sentence: He <highlight>landed</highlight> a number of film roles that finally got him noticed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他最终取得了一些让他引人注意的电影角色。

examination_example.sentence: It wasn't until 1980—32 years into his career—that he <highlight>landed</highlight> the role it would seem he was made for in Airplane!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到1980年，也就是他职业生涯的第32年，他才在《空前绝后满天飞》中获得了一个看起来很适合他的角色！

examination_example.sentence: A few minutes later, when I <highlight>landed</highlight> the trick, my friends beat their boards loud, shouting: "Safe! Safe! Safe!"
examination_example.sentence_trans: 几分钟后，当我完成这个动作时，我的朋友们大声拍打他们的滑板，喊道，“酷！酷！酷！”

examination_example.sentence: And that's what mattered—<highlight>landing</highlight> tricks, being a good skater.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这才是最重要的——落地技巧，成为一名优秀的溜冰者。

examination_example.sentence: That's to say, when we do something to the <highlight>land</highlight>, we should never hurt it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也就是说，当我们要对这片土地做一些事情时，我们也绝不应该伤害它。

examination_example.sentence: He intended to rob a poor woman of her <highlight>land</highlight>, her only stay and support after her husband died.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他企图抢走一个贫穷女人的土地，这是她丈夫死后她唯一的依靠和支持。

examination_example.sentence: Over the last ten years, China has made great efforts to green the <highlight>land</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在过去的十年里，中国为绿化土地付出了巨大的努力。

examination_example.sentence: We still know little about the Moon although men have <highlight>landed</highlight> on it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管人类已经登上月球，但我们对月球仍然知之甚少。

examination_example.sentence: Four days after <highlight>landing</highlight>, a tiny cotton shoot showed that they do.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 着陆后的第四天，一根细小的棉花枝表明它们确实如此。

examination_example.sentence: Sadly he died since his spaceship <highlight>landed</highlight> back on Earth.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 可悲的是，自从他的宇宙飞船回到地球后，他就去世了。

examination_example.sentence: As the world's third-longest river, it covers one-fifth of China's <highlight>land</highlight> area.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为世界上第三长的河流，它覆盖了中国陆地面积的五分之一。

examination_example.sentence: His book The Travel Notes of Xu Xiake provided important scientific information about the country's <highlight>land</highlight> and geography.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的著作《徐霞客游记》提供了关于该国土地和地理的重要科学信息。

examination_example.sentence: They live in the <highlight>Land</highlight> of Fruit.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们住在水果之国。

sense_info_list.en: the part of the earth's surface that is not covered by water, as opposed to the sea or the air

examination_example.sentence: However, the rough (汹涌的) waves made it too hard for Paul to push the boat to <highlight>land</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，汹涌的海浪让保罗很难把船推到岸边。

examination_example.sentence: I sometimes wondered how I could get to the <highlight>land</highlight> which was visible from the other side of the island.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有时我想知道怎样才能到达从岛的另一边就能看到的那片陆地。

examination_example.sentence: It can remain in the environment for many years and pollute large areas of <highlight>land</highlight> and water.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它可以在环境中保留多年，并且污染大面积的土地和水。

word_usage.usage: land作“土地、地产”时是不可数名词，表示“三片土地”时，应说three pieces of land。

land表示“国家，国土”时，是可数名词，其前常用介词in。
He travelled in many lands.
他在许多国家旅行过。

land作“上岸，着陆”时是不及物动词，后面如跟宾语，要加相应的介词。
示例：我们降落在芝加哥机场。
We landed at the airport in Chicago.
